OL,7,FA Policing Board statement said: "The
OL,8,Fboard chair and vice chair met with
OL,9,Fthe Chief Constable and impressed upon
OL,10,Fhim the damage that is being done to
OL,11,Fpublic confidence in policing as a
OL,12,Fresult of the revelations from the
OL,13,FInvestigatory Powers Tribunal.
OL,15,F"The Chief Constable has confirmed
OL,16,Fthat the board will be provided at its
OL,17,FJune meeting with a report on the
OL,18,Fextent of the surveillance of legal
OL,19,Fprofessionals and journalists, and
OL,20,Fthat this will be made public.
OL,26,@oD@bOUwD@AOU
